				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Great article, Wilson. Love it.</p>
<p>I will add one point: if you take the time to get all this working one, you should be able to reuse it over and over again. Yes, getting the baseline grid right on the web is a bit tricker than it should be, but once you&#8217;d done it, it&#8217;s pretty easy to maintain.</p>
<p>Consider building a CSS typography framework that you can reuse from project to project. We&#8217;ve recently done this at my day job, and it&#8217;s been really, really handy. Every project overrides certain aspects of the framework, but having a great starting point that already establishes a nice baseline grid is a huge time saver.</p>
<p>Great work, my friend.</p>
