					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://alistapart.com/article/settingtypeontheweb/#comment-11243">
							<time datetime="2007-04-10T22:03:00-04:00">
								April 10, 2007 at 10:03 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I am familiar with unitless line-heights and use them a lot. But since they adapt relative to the size of the text they don&#8217;t really solve the problem of maintaining a consistent line-height as the text size changes. For example, a line-height value of 1.5 with no unit will calculate to an 18px line-height for 12px text, and a 15px line-height for 10px text.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

