				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>bq. Really? I&#8217;d love to see some stats on that&#8221;¦ 🙂</p>
<p>Heh. I wish. I admit that I&#8217;m just making an edcated guess. We have no way of now how many of those IE6 users actually need to resize their text. But, it&#8217;s safe to assume it&#8217;s a pretty small number, isn&#8217;t it? If we, as good designers, are choosing reasonable font sizes to begin with, then it ought to only be people with low vision and no glasses to accomodate for it that really *need* to resize text, right?</p>
