				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>1. That person you&#8217;re shutting out of your site is one of the biggest taggers on del.icio.us, and their personal blog has a high Google page rank.  Wouldn&#8217;t you like a link from them?<br />
2. Your competition doesn&#8217;t use px on their site.</p>
<p>Actually, I note the example page in this article with the grid showing doesn&#8217;t line up on the grid once you get a certain part of the way down the page.  Firefox 2.0.0.3, default font Verdana 16, minimum font Verdana 14.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-11264" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-11264" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
