					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://alistapart.com/article/settingtypeontheweb/#comment-11264">
							<time datetime="2007-06-14T11:46:06-04:00">
								June 14, 2007 at 11:46 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I wrote some &#8220;Javascript&#8221;:<a href="http://societe-electronique.de/javascripts/theme/setting_type_on_the_web_to_a_baseline_grid.js" rel="nofollow ugc">http://societe-electronique.de/javascripts/theme/setting_type_on_the_web_to_a_baseline_grid.js</a> to auto-adjust image padding to fit the image to the grid. Adding some background and border; viola. (No example though; that blog is to new..)</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

