						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I have been working with a baseline grid ever since I read this article. I have found a few things I don&#8217;t care about, and have had some problems finding a work-a-round, but all that aside, I like the way it looks on a page, and have kept it.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m still new to the EM world, so I have been using pixels for a long time now.  </p>
<p>One question&#8230; why can&#8217;t font sizes in px be resized? And why can&#8217;t the line-height be adjusted upon resizing on of the text?</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t have IE6 installed these days, so I have no idea of the problems px fonts cause. I guess I should up my reading knowledge!</p>
<p>Anyways, great work. It was a good read!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

